radiographic_examinations.findings: Transabdominal examination demonstrates a slightly enlarged peripartum uterus measuring 13.4 x 5.4 x 7.7 cm. The endometrium is normal measuring 2 mm. A trace amount of simple fluid is identified within the endometrial canal, not an unexpected finding. No hyperechoic foci identified within the endometrial canal to suggest retained products of conception. Bilateral ovaries are normal in size and appearance. No free fluid identified.
